{"TopicId":217887,"ForumId":119,"TopicTitle":"About the trail of rocket engines","CreatedByName":"markyy","CreatedById":229361,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T05:55:12Z","PageNum":1,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"markyy","CreatedById":229361,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T05:55:12Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nAfter the release of patch 0.1.3, while launching another rocket (this time with more FPS), I noticed a rather strange behavior of the trail from the rocket engines.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022giphy.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExMGt0c2p1NWZleGpjMmFqNXlwdnU5c3BrdjB5NzBsbWdvNmUyaHdsdiZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/CK2wbxTqnwRio7vKH6/giphy.gif\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf someone hasn\u0027t guessed, I mean turning this trail along with the rocket.\u003Cbr\u003E\nI have little experience in unity development and I understand why it works this way and how it is implemented.\u003Cbr\u003E\nBut, imagine how cool it would be if the trace from the engines did not rotate with the rocket and followed the laws of physics, or, at least, had its own inertia\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022eMBZP2y.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022128.22\u0022 height=\u0022527\u0022 width=\u0022411\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/eMBZP2y.png\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\nI mean... guys.. ksp1 already works this way\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022giphy-downsized-large.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002256.25\u0022 height=\u0022270\u0022 width=\u0022480\u0022 src=\u0022https://media.giphy.com/media/v1.Y2lkPTc5MGI3NjExdHJ1Z2psZ2Rnc3hjazdna244b2ZtcTJqaHBkaDhrd2xhM2p3bXhycyZlcD12MV9pbnRlcm5hbF9naWZfYnlfaWQmY3Q9Zw/dkGdbRcc0FqmiqKahG/giphy-downsized-large.gif\u0022\u003E\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nThis behavior will be implemented, yea?..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-23T05:56:11Z\u0022 title=\u002206/23/2023 05:56  AM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 23, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by markyy\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"dr.phees","CreatedById":32383,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T09:58:40Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHahaha! Thanks for posting!!\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Superfluous J","CreatedById":73725,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T11:02:37Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224296136\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217887\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221687499712\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022229361\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022markyy\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n5 hours ago, markyy said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI mean... guys.. ksp1 already works this way\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo much for \u0022they just copied KSP1\u0027s code\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Spicat","CreatedById":228085,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T11:16:59Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey did a system for that sometimes ago:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022108.88\u0022 height=\u00221146\u0022 style=\u0022width:800px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221053\u0022 alt=\u0022exhaustbend.gif.d69b2bdf83caa42c6dedc0e1e3e56524.gif\u0022 src=\u0022https://kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2021_10/exhaustbend.gif.d69b2bdf83caa42c6dedc0e1e3e56524.gif\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe it wasn\u0027t good enough for them and decided to scrap it for now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe also know they will work on plumes again (From Nate Simpson):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cimg alt=\u0022lDkDGgf.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage\u0022 data-ratio=\u002212.07\u0022 height=\u002281\u0022 width=\u0022671\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/lDkDGgf.png\u0022\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSource for the gif above:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022216576\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed5823990446\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/204884-developer-insights-11-%E2%80%93-engine-exhaust-visual-effects/?do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4040143\u0026amp;embedComment=4040143\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:297px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"markyy","CreatedById":229361,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T11:44:04Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224296262\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217887\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221687519019\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022228085\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Spicat\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n13 minutes ago, Spicat said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nThey did a system for that sometimes ago:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2021_10/exhaustbend.gif.d69b2bdf83caa42c6dedc0e1e3e56524.gif\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022exhaustbend.gif.d69b2bdf83caa42c6dedc0e1e3e56524.gif\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u0022108.88\u0022 height=\u00221146\u0022 style=\u0022width:800px;height:auto;\u0022 width=\u00221053\u0022 src=\u0022https://kerbal-forum-uploads.s3.us-west-2.amazonaws.com/monthly_2021_10/exhaustbend.gif.d69b2bdf83caa42c6dedc0e1e3e56524.gif\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMaybe it wasn\u0027t good enough for them and decided to scrap it for now.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nWe also know they will work on plumes again (From Nate Simpson):\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Ca data-fileid=\u0022undefined\u0022 href=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/lDkDGgf.png\u0022 title=\u0022Enlarge image\u0022 rel=\u0022external nofollow\u0022\u003E\u003Cimg alt=\u0022lDkDGgf.png\u0022 class=\u0022ipsImage ipsImage_thumbnailed\u0022 data-ratio=\u002212.07\u0022 height=\u002281\u0022 width=\u0022671\u0022 src=\u0022https://i.imgur.com/lDkDGgf.png\u0022\u003E\u003C/a\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSource for the gif above:\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Ciframe allowfullscreen=\u0022\u0022 data-controller=\u0022core.front.core.autosizeiframe\u0022 data-embedauthorid=\u0022216576\u0022 data-embedcontent=\u0022\u0022 data-embedid=\u0022embed4803747599\u0022 src=\u0022https://forum.kerbalspaceprogram.com/topic/204884-developer-insights-11-%E2%80%93-engine-exhaust-visual-effects/?do=embed\u0026amp;comment=4040143\u0026amp;embedComment=4040143\u0026amp;embedDo=findComment\u0022 style=\u0022height:297px;max-width:502px;\u0022\u003E\u003C/iframe\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI think it\u0027s more about visuals than physical behavior and in the gif above, most likely just the effect of the direction of the thrust vector, but not the rotation of the rocket itself. Also noticed that they using mesh scaling, it\u0027s impossible to implement KSP1 smoke\u0027s behavior with mesh scaling, they\u0027ll have to use particles and it is a lot of work, if current smoke also works with mesh scaling as fire plume\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"markyy","CreatedById":229361,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T12:15:23Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00224296254\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u0022217887\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221687518157\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u002273725\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022Superfluous J\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n1 hour ago, Superfluous J said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nSo much for \u0022they just copied KSP1\u0027s code\u0022\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt would be much better if it were true..\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222023-06-23T12:15:47Z\u0022 title=\u002206/23/2023 12:15  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00221 yr\u0022\u003EJune 23, 2023\u003C/time\u003E by markyy\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Aaron VFX","CreatedById":216576,"CreatedDateTime":"2023-06-23T22:22:09Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nHi All,\u003Cbr\u003E\nGood call out. This is on the list.\u003Cbr\u003E\n\u003Cbr\u003E\nAttaching the particles to the local space of the engine is not the intended final result. We will improve engine exhaust effects in the future. What may seem like a straightforward solution gets really tricky under the hood.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}